      • AdsPortCloseEx

        public static Result AdsPortCloseEx(long port)
        The connection (communication port) to the message router is closed. The port to be closed must previously have been opened via an AdsPortOpenEx() call.
        Parameters:
        port - port number of an Ads port that had previously been opened with AdsPortOpenEx().
        Returns:
        [ADS Return Code](http://infosys.beckhoff.de/content/1033/tc3_adsdll2/html/ads_returncodes.htm?id=17663)

      • AdsPortOpenEx

        public static long AdsPortOpenEx()
        Establishes a connection (communication port) to the message router. The port number returned by AdsPortOpenEx() is required as parameter for further AdsLib function calls.
        Returns:
        port number of a new Ads port or 0 if no more ports available

      • AdsSyncReadDeviceInfoReqEx

        public static Result AdsSyncReadDeviceInfoReqEx(long port,
                                                org.apache.commons.lang3.tuple.ImmutablePair<AmsNetId,AmsPort> pAddr,
                                                Output<String> devName,
                                                Output<org.apache.commons.lang3.tuple.Triple<Byte,Byte,Integer>> version)
        Reads the identification and version number of an ADS server.
        Parameters:
        port - port number of an Ads port that had previously been opened with AdsPortOpenEx().
        pAddr - Structure with NetId and port number of the ADS server.
        devName - Pointer to a character string of at least 16 bytes, that will receive the name of the ADS device.
        version - Address of a variable of type AdsVersion, which will receive the version number, revision number and the build number.
        Returns:
        [ADS Return Code](http://infosys.beckhoff.de/content/1033/tc3_adsdll2/html/ads_returncodes.htm?id=17663)

      • AdsSyncAddDeviceNotificationReqEx

        public static Result AdsSyncAddDeviceNotificationReqEx(long port,
                                                       org.apache.commons.lang3.tuple.ImmutablePair<AmsNetId,AmsPort> pAddr,
                                                       IndexGroup indexGroup,
                                                       IndexOffset indexOffset,
                                                       AdsLib.AdsNotificationAttribute attribute,
                                                       AdsLib.PAdsNotificationFuncEx pFunc,
                                                       int hUser,
                                                       Output<Long> pNotification)
        A notification is defined within an ADS server (e.g. PLC). When a certain event occurs a function (the callback function) is invoked in the ADS client (C program).
        Parameters:
        port - port number of an Ads port that had previously been opened with AdsPortOpenEx().
        pAddr - Structure with NetId and port number of the ADS server.
        indexGroup - Index Group.
        indexOffset - Index Offset.
        attribute - Pointer to the structure that contains further information.
        pFunc - Pointer to the structure describing the callback function.
        hUser - 32-bit value that is passed to the callback function.
        pNotification - Address of the variable that will receive the handle of the notification.
        Returns:
        [ADS Return Code](http://infosys.beckhoff.de/content/1033/tc3_adsdll2/html/ads_returncodes.htm?id=17663)
